race.comment: INTERJECTION (5) taken back from the wide gate and never a genuine contender when fourth to Althoff over 1400m at Randwick. Gets the right set-up for this with a fast pace guaranteed. Can turn it around quickly on the backup. SOVEREIGN HILL (10) finally put it all together first-up with a convincing 5 len victory over 1250m at Canterbury in BM72 grade. Finds a tougher contest here with plenty of pressure. Will take catching. NO DRAMA (4) talented sprinter with excellent fresh credentials. Stalked the fast tempo with a decisive win over 1200m at Wyong. Jumps in weight but can get the job done again. OFF THE PRESS (7) gone to a new level this time in and deserves his chance in this tougher event. Covered a stack of ground in the run and failed to shirk his task with a narrow second over 1400m at Randwick Kensington. Braith Nock sticks and can take a hand in the finish. HANAU (6) set to peak third-up after catching the eye when fourth at Wyong. Worth thought with Rawiller aboard.
